main event: A woman in Warrenville, Illinois reported seeing a UFO on August 12, 1963.
interesting points: The object was visible for about 20-30 seconds.
It moved slowly in a southeasterly direction and flashed several times before disappearing.
Another witness, a bank manager, also observed the same phenomenon.
The object appeared solid and did not resemble an airplane or satellite.
The sighting was reported to Lt. Col. Robert Friend at the Wright-Patterson Air Force Base.
sighted object: a solid, slowly moving object that flashed several times
